## Responsive Tables

### 1. Horizontal Scroll

```css
.table-container {
  overflow-x: auto;
  -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
}

table {
  min-width: 600px;
}
```

**Pros**: Simple, preserves table structure
**Cons**: Not ideal for accessibility, can hide content

### 2. Stacked Layout

```css
/* Mobile: Stack rows */
@media (max-width: 767px) {
  table, thead, tbody, th, td, tr {
    display: block;
  }
  
  thead {
    display: none;
  }
  
  tr {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
  }
  
  td {
    text-align: right;
    padding-left: 50%;
    position: relative;
  }
  
  td::before {
    content: attr(data-label);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    width: 50%;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    text-align: left;
  }
}
```

```html
<tr>
  <td data-label="Name">John Doe</td>
  <td data-label="Email">john@example.com</td>
